replies.bodyText:
Usually for a public interface/class and a public method the method signature would have to stay the same except for between major version. In that case I would propose to introduce a new method, mark this one as deprecated and then we can remove it in 4.0.0 release.
However, if it's an actual bug where the queryBindings should have been provided and are required for this method to function correctly, then I'm not sure.
@jeenbroekstra should decide if that is the case.
